id: pm-2xwh
title: "Search: persistent search.hybrid_semantic_weight setting as default for pm search --semantic-weight"
description: "The per-query --semantic-weight override (pm-cy8i, closed) was shipped. The persistent search.hybrid_semantic_weight setting applies as the project default without specifying it on every query, so agents/users who want a consistent hybrid bias no longer must pass --semantic-weight on every invocation."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[4]: "area:search",config,hybrid,relevance
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:05:24.769Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-14T16:43:22.341Z"
author: audit-data-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- search.hybrid_semantic_weight: number (0..1) in PmSettings (under search, not search.tuning)\n- settings-validator support; config nested-settings alias search_hybrid_semantic_weight (ratio kind)\n- pm search uses the settings value as default when --semantic-weight is not passed\n- Contract / MCP contract table updated\n- pm config set search_hybrid_semantic_weight 0.7 works end-to-end"
parent: pm-ydp6
risk: low
confidence: high
resolution: Verified already-implemented persistent search.hybrid_semantic_weight setting works end-to-end
comments[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-06-14T16:23:39.448Z",maintainer-agent,"Verified already-implemented (resolver resolveHybridSemanticWeight reads search.hybrid_semantic_weight, settings-validator supports it, nested-settings descriptor search_hybrid_semantic_weight + ratio kind, runSearch uses it as --semantic-weight default). Confirmed end-to-end in sandbox: config set search_hybrid_semantic_weight 0.85 persists + applies. Never documented in CHANGELOG (only per-query pm-cy8i was) -> closing here surfaces the persistent setting. No new code needed."
close_reason: Verified already-implemented persistent search.hybrid_semantic_weight setting works end-to-end
body: "## Context\n\nThe per-query `--semantic-weight` override (pm-cy8i) shipped earlier. The persistent `search.hybrid_semantic_weight` setting (under `search`, not `search.tuning`) lets teams persist a hybrid bias as the project default.\n\n## Acceptance criteria (verified already-implemented)\n\n- [x] `search.hybrid_semantic_weight: number (0..1)` in PmSettings.search\n- [x] settings-validator support + nested-settings alias `search_hybrid_semantic_weight` (ratio kind)\n- [x] pm search uses it as the `--semantic-weight` default when the flag is omitted\n- [x] Contract / MCP contract table cover it\n- [x] `pm config set search_hybrid_semantic_weight 0.7` works end-to-end\n\n## Evidence\n\n- resolveHybridSemanticWeight reads search.hybrid_semantic_weight (default 0.7); used at runSearch semantic-weight resolution."
